# Thunderbolt Project Cursor Rules

## Input Component Rules

### Placeholder Fill Enforcement
When creating Input or TextArea components with placeholders, you MUST enable the placeholder fill feature for better UX:

**✅ CORRECT:**
```tsx
<Input
  label="Job Name"
  placeholder="e.g., Metering and Stop Button"
  enablePlaceholderFill={true}
/>
```

**❌ INCORRECT:**
```tsx
<Input
  label="Job Name"
  placeholder="e.g., Metering and Stop Button"
/>
```

**Why this matters:**
- Placeholder fill buttons (⚡ lightning bolt icon) provide one-click value insertion
- Improves user experience by reducing typing for common values
- Ensures consistent UX across all forms in the app
- Follows established patterns used throughout the codebase

### Enforcement Rules:
1. **Any `<Input>` or `<TextArea>` with a `placeholder` prop MUST have `enablePlaceholderFill={true}`**
2. **Exception:** Components without placeholders don't need this prop
3. **Exception:** When placeholder fill would be inappropriate (passwords, search fields, etc.)

### Common Patterns to Check:
- ✅ Form inputs in Admin panel (job creation, equipment, etc.)
- ✅ Test creation forms (test names, input labels, units)
- ✅ Asset management forms (properties, notes)
- ✅ Any user-facing input with helpful placeholder examples

### How to Use:
1. Add a descriptive placeholder that shows the expected format
2. Always include `enablePlaceholderFill={true}`
3. The lightning bolt (⚡) will appear automatically when placeholder exists

### Cursor Auto-fix:
When you create an Input/TextArea with `placeholder="..."` but no `enablePlaceholderFill`, Cursor will suggest adding `enablePlaceholderFill={true}`.

### Examples from Codebase:
```tsx
// ✅ Good - Test name input with placeholder fill
<Input
  label="Test Name"
  placeholder="e.g., VT winding resistance test"
  enablePlaceholderFill={true}
  required
/>

// ✅ Good - Unit input with placeholder fill
<Input
  label="Unit"
  placeholder="e.g., V, Ω, A"
  enablePlaceholderFill={true}
/>

// ❌ Bad - Missing enablePlaceholderFill
<Input
  label="Test Name"
  placeholder="e.g., VT winding resistance test"
/>
```
